r $52,000.00 was owed to the state. Doesn't the DOA and CFW work for the same state? If so, how can funding an agency already in arrears to the state be in good judgement?  Any way, I choose not to join in the conferrence call with Chilton as it will be a waste of my time. These issues have already cost me well more than it's been worth. I will be continuing to gather information on on the grant funding of Options. Your cooperation in complying will be appreciated. Someone needs to track tax dollar expenditures by this agency. The economy is too fragile for the state to issue grand funds and to not account for them. Andy Midyette

